# Force LF line endings on checkout for every text file in the repo.
#
# This matters because all our containers run Linux, but Windows Git can
# silently rewrite files to CRLF on checkout (its default for any .sh, .py,
# Dockerfile, etc). That produces shell errors like:
#   /bin/bash^M: bad interpreter: No such file or directory
# inside the container — incredibly confusing because the file *looks* fine
# in the editor.
#
# `text=auto eol=lf` says "auto-detect text vs binary, and for text use LF
# regardless of host OS." This is the standard hardening for repos that
# build Docker images on Linux but get cloned by mixed-OS contributors.

*               text=auto eol=lf

# Be explicit about scripts and config that *must* stay LF — these files
# are the ones that break loudest if CRLF sneaks in.
*.sh            text eol=lf
*.py            text eol=lf
*.yml           text eol=lf
*.yaml          text eol=lf
*.conf          text eol=lf
*.env           text eol=lf
Dockerfile      text eol=lf
Dockerfile.*    text eol=lf

# Explicit binary so Git doesn't try to diff/munge them.
*.png           binary
*.jpg           binary
*.jpeg          binary
*.gif           binary
*.ico           binary
*.pdf           binary
*.docx          binary
*.xlsx          binary
*.zip           binary
*.gz            binary
*.tar           binary
*.tgz           binary
*.woff          binary
*.woff2         binary
*.ttf           binary
*.eot           binary
